{"questionId":"3307202","questionHtml":"<p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> that maximizes the volume of the box.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to sketch the function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> with indication of maximum&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/a3ab1767551d00340274b3dc1365ebbbfd6b0b13.png\"></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>recognition of setting the derivative to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>e.g. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>cm</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)A0</strong></em> for the maximum given as a coordinate pair.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3307202","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ1.7b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the value of x that maximizes the volume of the box.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.6—Stationary points, local max and min","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.4—Key features of graphs, intersections using technology","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sect